WEBVTT

1
00:00:36.400 --> 00:00:39.400
Quality over Quantity (QoQ) Releases
Hacksaw Ridge (2016)

2
00:00:39.500 --> 00:00:41.700
Translation: RQ
Control: Scarlett

3
00:00:42.700 --> 00:00:46.400
A TRUE STORY

4
00:01:45.600 --> 00:01:47.901
Didn't you hear it?

5
00:01:48.001 --> 00:01:50.469
An eternal God is the Lord....

6
00:01:50.569 --> 00:01:53.191
Creator of the ends of the earth.

7
00:01:54.461 --> 00:01:57.812
He doesn't get tired, He doesn't get exhausted....

8
00:01:57.912 --> 00:02:00.876
His wisdom is unfathomable.

9
00:02:05.208 --> 00:02:11.010
He gives strength to the weary,
the powerless he gives power in abundance.

10
00:02:11.110 --> 00:02:15.451
Young fighters get tired and exhausted....

11
00:02:15.551 --> 00:02:20.151
but those who hope in the Lord receive new strength:

12
00:02:22.046 --> 00:02:24.823
They spread their wings like eagles....

13
00:02:24.923 --> 00:02:27.443
they run, but do not get exhausted....

14
00:02:27.543 --> 00:02:30.681
they walk, but don't get tired.

15
00:02:32.352 --> 00:02:35.582
Desmond, hang in there.

16
00:02:36.382 --> 00:02:42.347
Hang in there, Desmond. We're going to get you out of here.

17
00:02:49.156 --> 00:02:51.459
BLUE RIDGE MOUNTAINS, VIRGINIA

18
00:02:52.285 --> 00:02:55.146
SIXTEEN YEARS EARLIER

19
00:02:56.173 --> 00:02:59.977
Desmond.

20
00:03:00.528 --> 00:03:02.589
What?
- Now wait.

21
00:03:02.740 --> 00:03:06.870
Walk on.
- Just wait. I have to tell you something.

22
00:03:10.483 --> 00:03:12.092
What then, Hal?

23
00:03:12.986 --> 00:03:16.122
Whoever gets to the top first.
- Cheater.

24
00:03:25.878 --> 00:03:27.621
See you later, slugger.

25
00:03:34.947 --> 00:03:37.374
Should I help?
- I'll manage.

26
00:03:43.742 --> 00:03:45.686
Sit down.
- Stop.

27
00:03:45.795 --> 00:03:47.096
Stop yourself.

28
00:03:51.385 --> 00:03:53.003
For heaven's sake.

29
00:03:54.030 --> 00:03:58.393
Get away from the edge.
You're going to break your necks.

30
00:04:00.213 --> 00:04:03.725
Those are the Doss brothers.
Just as crazy as their dad.

31
00:04:12.187 --> 00:04:15.548
They are on the corner of Jackson and Main
digging.

32
00:04:17.448 --> 00:04:19.501
They are laying a sidewalk.

33
00:04:22.401 --> 00:04:25.102
You would not know it again.

34
00:04:31.769 --> 00:04:34.557
And I doubt they would recognize you.

35
00:04:36.657 --> 00:04:39.846
They barely recognize me when I walk past them.

36
00:04:42.225 --> 00:04:44.669
Like I died with you.

37
00:04:49.943 --> 00:04:52.595
As if we never existed.

38
00:05:01.249 --> 00:05:04.513
That's all I have for you today.

39
00:05:24.403 --> 00:05:26.989
Block him with the right, Desmond.

40
00:05:27.524 --> 00:05:29.734
Stop it. Do you guys hear me?

41
00:05:30.845 --> 00:05:33.457
Why do they fight?
- Do they need a reason for that?

42
00:05:33.640 --> 00:05:34.900
Tom, do...

43
00:05:35.543 --> 00:05:39.897
Why should I stop them? Now all I have to do
give the one who wins a beating.

44
00:05:48.392 --> 00:05:51.730
Wake up. Can you hear me?
- What have you done?

45
00:05:51.871 --> 00:05:53.281
He doesn't hear me.

46
00:05:55.886 --> 00:05:57.452
I'll get some ice cream.

47
00:06:00.307 --> 00:06:03.102
Can you put that basket away?
- I will.

48
00:06:04.202 --> 00:06:05.672
Is he still breathing?

49
00:06:06.624 --> 00:06:09.702
Hal? Hal, can you hear me?

50
00:06:25.239 --> 00:06:27.007
He has dilated pupils.

51
00:06:50.221 --> 00:06:52.904
What are you working on?

52
00:06:53.804 --> 00:06:59.804
You're going to get a beating. You know the rules.

53
00:07:00.804 --> 00:07:03.104
Do you hear me, Desmond?

54
00:07:03.204 --> 00:07:04.704
SIXTH GOD
THOU SHALT NOT KILL

55
00:07:05.782 --> 00:07:11.222
Hold on. What will he learn from that?
He's fierce enough already.

56
00:07:11.723 --> 00:07:17.564
Just smother him with kisses. Tell him
That the world is a tender and sweet place.

57
00:07:21.928 --> 00:07:24.005
Hal will be fine.

58
00:07:40.326 --> 00:07:44.237
I could have beaten him to death.
- Yes, you could have.

59
00:07:44.928 --> 00:07:47.628
Murder is the greatest sin.

60
00:07:47.728 --> 00:07:53.028
Taking someone's life,
is the greatest sin in God's eyes.

61
00:07:53.128 --> 00:07:55.728
Nothing hurts Him anymore.

62
00:07:56.805 --> 00:08:01.215
Don't you understand English?
Do I have to say it again?

63
00:08:01.715 --> 00:08:05.601
Otherwise, I'll kick your ass....
- What's going on in there? Are you all right, Bertha?

64
00:08:05.701 --> 00:08:09.286
Mind your own business.
- Don't take it out on...

65
00:08:10.573 --> 00:08:12.324
I hate it.

66
00:08:27.444 --> 00:08:28.662
Mama?

67
00:08:41.362 --> 00:08:43.973
Why does he hate us so much?

68
00:08:44.941 --> 00:08:47.504
He doesn't hate us.

69
00:08:49.404 --> 00:08:53.204
He hates himself. Sometimes.

70
00:08:54.404 --> 00:08:57.004
Your father was not himself tonight.

71
00:08:58.304 --> 00:09:01.904
I wish you would know him
As I knew him before the war.

72
00:09:02.473 --> 00:09:05.901
praise the Lord, praise the Lord....

73
00:09:08.914 --> 00:09:11.693
FIFTEEN YEARS LATER

74
00:09:25.043 --> 00:09:29.106
How did we sound, Desmond?
- Like heavenly angels, ma.

75
00:09:29.215 --> 00:09:32.594
You know lying is a sin,
especially in this place.

76
00:09:32.787 --> 00:09:35.355
I didn't say they were singing angels.

77
00:09:40.755 --> 00:09:43.024
What's going on there?

78
00:09:43.175 --> 00:09:44.776
Lift.

79
00:09:47.596 --> 00:09:49.590
Drag it out from under it. Just the rug.

80
00:09:54.873 --> 00:09:59.395
I call an ambulance.
- No time. Joshua's pickup. Quickly.

81
00:10:14.295 --> 00:10:16.095
LYNCHBURG HOSPITAL

82
00:10:17.318 --> 00:10:20.930
You'll be fine. You're in good hands.

83
00:10:23.142 --> 00:10:26.580
What do we have here?
A severed artery. Get the sutures.

84
00:10:26.730 --> 00:10:29.767
Keep pressing it.
Did you apply this tourniquet?

85
00:10:30.084 --> 00:10:32.327
Well done.
You saved this boy's life.

86
00:10:33.322 --> 00:10:35.949
Will you stay with us? You'll be fine again.

87
00:10:36.092 --> 00:10:39.003
What's your name?
- Gilbert.

88
00:10:39.972 --> 00:10:43.801
Operate?
- Yes. Stay with us. You'll be fine.

89
00:11:50.269 --> 00:11:53.055
The army inspection is there. Blood is given here.

90
00:11:58.973 --> 00:12:00.398
Are you okay?

91
00:12:02.017 --> 00:12:05.416
Oh, that's not mine. I don't have anything.

92
00:12:06.016 --> 00:12:08.016
Still, thanks for asking.

93
00:12:12.615 --> 00:12:14.324
What do you need?

94
00:12:16.386 --> 00:12:17.715
My belt.

95
00:12:20.715 --> 00:12:23.615
I lent it to the boy
who had that accident.

96
00:12:23.715 --> 00:12:26.415
My pants don't stay on anymore.

97
00:12:27.542 --> 00:12:29.987
I don't have your belt.

98
00:12:30.170 --> 00:12:33.691
No, I know that. It's still there with that boy.

99
00:12:35.625 --> 00:12:39.323
I'm just taking blood here.
- I'm willing to give some too.

100
00:12:42.034 --> 00:12:45.230
Go to that room and wait with the others.
I will call you.

101
00:12:50.646 --> 00:12:51.847
That room.

102
00:12:59.841 --> 00:13:02.502
Have you given blood before, Mr....

103
00:13:04.096 --> 00:13:05.286
Doss.

104
00:13:06.486 --> 00:13:09.386
My friends call me Desmond.
No, this is the first time.

105
00:13:10.986 --> 00:13:13.086
RARE BIRDS OF NORTH AMERICA

106
00:13:18.064 --> 00:13:20.970
I always dreamed of
of becoming a doctor...

107
00:13:21.670 --> 00:13:23.570
but I didn't have much school.

108
00:13:25.641 --> 00:13:30.175
You may get a little dizzy.
Will you be picked up?

109
00:13:30.948 --> 00:13:34.768
No, I'm going to walk back.
- Where do you live?

110
00:13:35.320 --> 00:13:37.923
Fort Hill.
- That's quite a distance.

111
00:13:38.048 --> 00:13:40.345
Eight to ten kilometers.

112
00:13:40.845 --> 00:13:44.472
I go through the forest, then it's almost twelve.

113
00:13:45.374 --> 00:13:48.744
Then you must really like the forest.
- I certainly do.

114
00:13:50.079 --> 00:13:51.759
Keep pressing this.

115
00:13:52.959 --> 00:13:55.059
Is it going?
- Yes.

116
00:13:59.584 --> 00:14:02.888
Where do you go dressed up like this?

117
00:14:03.063 --> 00:14:04.669
I met someone yesterday.

118
00:14:04.769 --> 00:14:07.569
A nurse, Dorothy Schutte.
I'm going to marry her.

119
00:14:07.736 --> 00:14:11.465
Does she know this herself?
- Not yet, but she will soon.

120
00:14:11.599 --> 00:14:15.771
Have you ever talked to a woman?
One who is not a relative?

121
00:14:15.913 --> 00:14:17.180
Talked to her.

122
00:14:18.316 --> 00:14:21.469
In that case... Come give your brother a hug.

123
00:14:21.654 --> 00:14:23.660
Get rid of those fat claws.

124
00:14:25.160 --> 00:14:27.035
Wish me luck, Ma.

125
00:14:27.135 --> 00:14:28.335
Success.

126
00:15:05.518 --> 00:15:06.735
Next.

127
00:15:06.894 --> 00:15:09.923
Sit down. Have you given blood before?

128
00:15:10.107 --> 00:15:11.525
Yes.

129
00:15:14.387 --> 00:15:17.515
You are that man of the belt.
- Desmond.

130
00:15:17.658 --> 00:15:20.379
Desmond, you can't
give blood two days in a row.

131
00:15:20.520 --> 00:15:23.557
Nice. I've come to take mine back.
- Excuse me, sir?

132
00:15:23.733 --> 00:15:25.350
My blood. I want it back.

133
00:15:26.593 --> 00:15:29.173
That's not how it works.
We can't just give it back.

134
00:15:29.323 --> 00:15:35.050
You have to. Ever since you stuck me
with that syringe, my heart has been racing.

135
00:15:35.150 --> 00:15:38.050
Every time I think of you,
it makes it tick even more.

136
00:15:39.669 --> 00:15:42.798
I didn't know that one yet. Pretty banal.

137
00:15:42.965 --> 00:15:44.290
Really?

138
00:15:44.790 --> 00:15:47.790
Too bad. I've been practicing on that all night.

139
00:15:48.290 --> 00:15:49.490
Not good?

140
00:15:51.418 --> 00:15:53.052
I didn't say that.

141
00:16:13.171 --> 00:16:16.315
What is the difference
between an artery and a vein?

142
00:16:18.260 --> 00:16:21.631
What are you talking about?
- The accident of that boy.

143
00:16:23.935 --> 00:16:25.702
Arteries squirt blood.

144
00:16:27.330 --> 00:16:28.640
And veins?

145
00:16:30.250 --> 00:16:31.493
Bleeding.

146
00:16:34.393 --> 00:16:38.493
I think you should practice at home on your
boy-girl conversation should practice.

147
00:16:38.661 --> 00:16:40.221
Probably so.

148
00:16:42.224 --> 00:16:44.768
I do have a book for you,
if you're so interested.

149
00:16:46.154 --> 00:16:47.539
About dating?

150
00:16:49.050 --> 00:16:50.626
About blood.

151
00:16:53.726 --> 00:16:55.326
PRELUDE TO WAR

152
00:16:58.762 --> 00:17:01.406
Another medical question?

153
00:17:01.540 --> 00:17:04.811
No, I just think you're the most beautiful
I've ever seen.

154
00:17:06.296 --> 00:17:08.440
That's because I'm in the dark.

155
00:17:11.411 --> 00:17:12.549
No...

156
00:17:13.949 --> 00:17:15.757
you are just gorgeous.

157
00:17:40.407 --> 00:17:41.824
On the side.

158
00:17:44.011 --> 00:17:46.196
You have to be careful where you walk.

159
00:17:57.945 --> 00:18:00.189
I'm sorry.
I didn't think you'd mind.

160
00:18:00.683 --> 00:18:02.192
You didn't ask.

161
00:18:03.061 --> 00:18:06.748
I thought you'd like it.
- Maybe I would, if you had asked.

162
00:18:17.437 --> 00:18:18.738
Are you coming?

163
00:18:21.317 --> 00:18:23.269
Be careful where you walk.

164
00:18:44.583 --> 00:18:46.443
Why didn't you say anything?

165
00:18:46.585 --> 00:18:49.487
Because you would try to talk me out of it.
I know I'm doing the right thing.

166
00:18:49.605 --> 00:18:53.700
What about His commandment?
- In war it is not to kill.

167
00:18:53.800 --> 00:18:56.800
It's protect. A lot of guys from our church go.

168
00:18:56.900 --> 00:18:59.500
There is war, and they need people.

169
00:18:59.600 --> 00:19:02.200
Working in a paper mill
is not going to save this country.

170
00:19:10.776 --> 00:19:14.820
Looks like a movie star, our boy.

171
00:19:17.620 --> 00:19:21.717
Nice uniform, good cap.

172
00:19:24.217 --> 00:19:28.597
Reminds me of Artie Giddens,
when we went to France.

173
00:19:30.422 --> 00:19:31.922
Do you remember him?
- Don't.

174
00:19:35.064 --> 00:19:38.605
I'm just saying
how good Artie looked in his uniform.

175
00:19:39.805 --> 00:19:42.230
At least you girls thought so.

176
00:19:42.330 --> 00:19:45.435
They came to him in droves,
and he was proud of that.

177
00:19:51.133 --> 00:19:54.839
I just hope that when Hal
gets shot, it's from the front.

178
00:19:55.739 --> 00:19:58.643
Like a regular gunshot wound, not much mess.

179
00:19:59.143 --> 00:20:05.243
Artie was shot in the back.
His intestines came out the front.

180
00:20:07.743 --> 00:20:10.243
His entire uniform went down.

181
00:20:13.906 --> 00:20:19.252
Fortunately, he was dead and never found out
how awful his uniform looked.

182
00:20:23.331 --> 00:20:25.000
Disappear from my eyes.

183
00:21:24.142 --> 00:21:26.453
Are you half climbing goat?

184
00:21:28.146 --> 00:21:32.942
Are you gonna help me, Desmond Doss,
or are you going to leave me here?

185
00:21:37.089 --> 00:21:40.350
I'll help you, for a price.
- What then?

186
00:21:41.393 --> 00:21:42.669
A kiss.

187
00:21:45.013 --> 00:21:50.199
That is pure blackmail.
- Yes, but that is the condition.

188
00:21:52.199 --> 00:21:53.599
That's the deal.

189
00:21:54.999 --> 00:21:56.699
I'm going to hold you to that.

190
00:22:09.562 --> 00:22:11.220
Wait a minute.

191
00:22:13.620 --> 00:22:18.020
You're not going to hit me, are you?
Because if I fall, I'll drag you down with me.

192
00:22:18.655 --> 00:22:20.581
Kiss me, and you'll know.

193
00:22:52.681 --> 00:22:56.681
HANDBOOK OF PRACTICAL ANATOMY

194
00:23:09.581 --> 00:23:10.772
What?

195
00:23:11.874 --> 00:23:13.697
I need to be employed.

196
00:23:14.897 --> 00:23:17.697
I can't stay here,
while they all go and fight for me.

197
00:23:17.814 --> 00:23:21.964
You can.
- I have to. I want to be a medic.

198
00:23:22.064 --> 00:23:24.511
Then I save people, instead of killing them.

199
00:23:28.450 --> 00:23:30.651
I have to work. I'm going to be late.

200
00:23:34.839 --> 00:23:37.574
Dorothy, honey. Dorothy.

201
00:23:40.837 --> 00:23:43.514
Are you going to ask me to marry you now?

202
00:23:45.780 --> 00:23:50.021
I don't know. Do you still want me then?
- I don't know. You didn't ask.

203
00:23:50.538 --> 00:23:52.504
I ask.

204
00:23:53.904 --> 00:23:59.455
With all my heart. Will you marry me?
- Then, yes, I will.

205
00:24:09.156 --> 00:24:11.936
When.
- As soon as you get leave.

206
00:24:12.036 --> 00:24:14.336
But I don't like you right now.

207
00:24:17.672 --> 00:24:19.225
But I do love you.

208
00:24:32.304 --> 00:24:34.323
Ma said I should come here to you.

209
00:24:39.823 --> 00:24:42.023
Those three were my best friends.

210
00:24:43.223 --> 00:24:45.023
I grew up with them.

211
00:24:45.923 --> 00:24:48.723
Got into trouble together,
chasing girls together.

212
00:24:49.123 --> 00:24:50.723
And joined together in service.

213
00:24:52.823 --> 00:24:54.623
Now my friends are lying there.

214
00:24:56.423 --> 00:24:59.923
Covered with earth and grass, eaten by worms.

215
00:25:02.523 --> 00:25:05.023
I don't want to come and see my sons here.

216
00:25:06.088 --> 00:25:08.823
Dad, I've already signed up.

217
00:25:11.323 --> 00:25:13.823
I couldn't help myself.

218
00:25:14.823 --> 00:25:18.104
All those others do...
- You are not like those others.

219
00:25:20.104 --> 00:25:26.104
All those others dive in without thinking,
just like the fools we were.

220
00:25:27.004 --> 00:25:31.004
The soldiers who stay alive,
stay alive because they can. You don't.

221
00:25:31.804 --> 00:25:34.504
You have to start thinking and praying about everything.

222
00:25:35.868 --> 00:25:38.715
Just look, you're doing it now too.

223
00:25:38.815 --> 00:25:43.138
You won't be able to live with yourself if you go.
- No, I won't be able to if I don't go.

224
00:25:43.238 --> 00:25:44.838
I'm going to be a medic.

225
00:25:45.638 --> 00:25:49.586
That's going to be my way of serving.
- There you go again, thinking about it.

226
00:25:50.186 --> 00:25:54.786
Do you think that war is going to
to you? To your ideas?

227
00:25:55.412 --> 00:25:57.806
No doubt it will be very tough.

228
00:25:59.600 --> 00:26:01.979
It's not going to be tough, it's going to be impossible.

229
00:26:02.779 --> 00:26:09.206
Whatever is going on in your crazy head,
it's not gonna be like that. It doesn't work that way.

230
00:26:09.806 --> 00:26:15.506
And should you by some miracle survive ,
you won't thank God for it.

231
00:26:20.506 --> 00:26:25.866
Breakup. Come on, guys, you're now
from Uncle Sam. Say hello to your mother.

232
00:26:26.866 --> 00:26:31.356
Come on. Ladies, please move away from that bus.
- Almost forgot.

233
00:26:31.456 --> 00:26:35.756
Should I get a crowbar?
- Here. This is for you.

234
00:26:35.856 --> 00:26:37.356
That one is mine.

235
00:26:39.156 --> 00:26:42.856
Keep it there, where I will be.

236
00:26:53.139 --> 00:26:54.443
I love you.

237
00:26:58.812 --> 00:27:00.512
BIBLE

238
00:27:10.612 --> 00:27:14.595
COME BACK TO ME, DESMOND DOSS
I LOVE YOU

239
00:27:36.360 --> 00:27:37.708
Sorry, mate.

240
00:27:44.871 --> 00:27:47.974
Do I have to look at your deformity every time
when I walk to my bed?

241
00:27:48.074 --> 00:27:50.674
Look at it with envy, my friend.

242
00:27:51.924 --> 00:27:54.643
What's up? You look lost.

243
00:27:54.743 --> 00:27:56.443
This one is still free.

244
00:27:56.575 --> 00:28:00.001
Wise Decision. Views of the mountains and lake.

245
00:28:00.501 --> 00:28:01.696
Randall Fuller.

246
00:28:03.139 --> 00:28:05.741
Desmond Doss.
- Just call him Teach, the teacher.

247
00:28:05.841 --> 00:28:09.466
Nobody understands what he is talking about.
- Because nobody here can read.

248
00:28:09.566 --> 00:28:12.666
